cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MM, cs.NE 

This paper is about weakly supervised semantic segmentation, which is a computer vision task. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also proposes a novel regularization method for the network, which involves learning from self-supervision, indicating that it may fall under the categories of machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Additionally, the paper involves experiments on image datasets, which could also place it under multimedia (cs.MM). Finally, the paper involves the use of neural networks, which could also place it under neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE).
